{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Selection API","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection_API","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection_API\">Selection API</a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Interfaces</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection\"><code>Selection</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/getSelection\"><code>Document.getSelection()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/getSelection\"><code>Window.getSelection()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/selectionchange_event\"><code>Document</code>: <code>selectionchange</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/selectstart_event\"><code>Document</code>: <code>selectstart</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> This API is <em>not available</em> in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Workers_API\">Web Workers</a> (not exposed via <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WorkerNavigator\"><code>WorkerNavigator</code></a>).</p>\n</div>\n<p>The <strong>Selection API</strong> enables developers to access and manipulate the portion of a document selected by the user.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/getSelection\" title=\"Window.getSelection()\"><code>Window.getSelection()</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/getSelection\" title=\"Document.getSelection()\"><code>Document.getSelection()</code></a> methods return a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection\"><code>Selection</code></a> object representing the portion of the document selected by the user. A <code>Selection</code> object provides methods to:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>access the currently selected nodes</li>\n  <li>modify the current selection, expanding or collapsing it or selecting an entirely different part of the document</li>\n  <li>delete parts of the current selection from the DOM.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The Selection API also provides two events, both firing on <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document\"><code>Document</code></a>:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Node/selectstart_event\" title=\"selectstart\"><code>selectstart</code></a> event is fired when the user starts to make a new selection</li>\n  <li>the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/selectionchange_event\" title=\"selectionchange\"><code>selectionchange</code></a> event is fired when the current selection changes.</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"interfaces","title":"Interfaces","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"selection\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection\"><code>Selection</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An interface which represents the part of the document selected by the user or the current position of the caret.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"document.getselection\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/getSelection\" title=\"Document.getSelection()\"><code>Document.getSelection()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A method returning a <code>Selection</code> object representing the current selection or current position of the caret.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"window.getselection\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/getSelection\" title=\"Window.getSelection()\"><code>Window.getSelection()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A method returning a <code>Selection</code> object representing the current selection or current position of the caret.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"document.selectionchange\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/selectionchange_event\" title=\"Document.selectionchange\"><code>Document.selectionchange</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An event which is fired when the current selection is changed.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"node.selectstart\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Node/selectstart_event\" title=\"Node.selectstart\"><code>Node.selectstart</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An event which is fired when a user starts a new selection.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/selection-api/#selection-interface","title":"Selection API"}],"query":"undefined"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Interfaces","id":"interfaces"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"}],"summary":"The Selection API enables developers to access and manipulate the portion of a document selected by the user.","popularity":0.0006,"modified":"2022-09-16T18:48:33.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"API Selection","locale":"fr","native":"Fran√ßais"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/selection_api","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/selection_api/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/26de76d3684b4c61684618cecb18e71c8fed93d5","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection_API","title":"Selection API"}],"pageTitle":"Selection API - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}